<br>
A guild has 24 hours to kill their Rotation Mob.<br>
<br>
If they &quot;pass&quot;, they have to inform, in a timely manner, the guild that follows them in the Rotation, who then have 24 hours from the time they are informed of the &quot;pass&quot;.  <br>
<br>
If they decide to &quot;let someone try&quot; on their turn, they don't necessarily have to &quot;pass&quot;.<br>
<br>
So it would be like such:<br>
<br>
Guilds A, B, C, D on Mob 1.<br>
<br>
Scenario 1:  Guild A kills, B now up.  B, without passing, decides to let Guild Y try Mob 1.   Guild Y goes in, kills.  B is still up next.  The Rotation is then A, Y, B, C, D.<br>
<br>
Scenario 2:  Guild A kills, B now up.  B, without passing decides to let Guild Y try Mob 1.  Guild Z races Guild Y, and wins. B is still up next.   The Rotation is then A, Z, B, C, D. <br>
<br>
Scenario 3:  Guild A kills, B now up.  Before B can get to the mob, Guild Z goes in, kills.  B is still up next.  The Rotation is then A, Z, B, C, D.<br>
<br>
Scenario 4:  Guild A kills, B now up.  B passes. C now up.  The Rotation is still A, B, C, D.<br>
<br>
Any guild, not on the Rotation, has the chance to break into a Rotation at any time, and don't need 'permission' from those in the Rotation.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utils.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tils</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.loopi.co.uk/bounce.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/9/02 8:56:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.loopi.co.uk/tils2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about Planes + 1</span><hr size=1> In nycas examples...<br>
